<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 15 at 6:03PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 630 PM EDT
FOR MONROE COUNTY...
At 603 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Monroe, moving
east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
Monroe County, including the following locations... Newport, Samaria,
Estral Beach, Toledo Beach, Scofield, Erie, South Rockwood, Woodland
Beach, Stony Point and La Salle.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
